43void MySQLDataStore::loadAdditionalTableConfig()
44{
45 // add all defined ascemu tables to addition table loading
46 for (const auto& ascTables : ascemuTables)
47 {
48 MySQLAdditionalTable myTable;
49 myTable.mainTable = ascTables;
50 myTable.tableVector.push_back(ascTables);
51
52 // get config
53 const std::string strData = worldConfig.startup.additionalTableLoads;
54 if (!strData.empty())
55 {
56 const std::vector<std::string> strs = AscEmu::Util::Strings::split(strData, ",");
57 if (!strs.empty())
58 {
59 for (auto& str : strs)
60 {
61 std::stringstream additionTableStream(str);
62 std::string additional_table;
63 std::string target_table;
64
65 additionTableStream >> additional_table;
66 additionTableStream >> target_table;
67
68 if (!additional_table.empty() || !target_table.empty())
69 {
70 if (myTable.mainTable == target_table)
71 {
72 if (auto result = WorldDatabase.Query("SELECT COUNT(*) FROM information_schema.tables WHERE table_schema = \"%s\" AND table_name = \"%s\"", WorldDatabase.GetDatabaseName().c_str(), additional_table.c_str()))
73 {
74 Field* fields = result->Fetch();
75
76 uint32_t count = fields[0].asUint32();
77 if (fields[0].asUint32())
78 myTable.tableVector.push_back(additional_table);
79 else
80 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Additional table `{}` defined in world.conf does not exist!", additional_table);
81 }
82 }
83 }
84 }
85 }
86 }
87
88 MySQLAdditionalTables.push_back(myTable);
89 }
90
91 for (auto additionalTable : MySQLAdditionalTables)
92 {
93 sLogger.debugFlag(AscEmu::Logging::DebugFlags::LF_DB_TABLES, "MySQLDataLoads : Table {} has additional tables:", additionalTable.mainTable);
94 for (auto additionalTableList : additionalTable.tableVector)
95 sLogger.debugFlag(AscEmu::Logging::DebugFlags::LF_DB_TABLES, "MySQLDataLoads : - {} ", additionalTableList);
96 }
97}

99std::unique_ptr<QueryResult> MySQLDataStore::getWorldDBQuery(const char* query, ...)
100{
101 // fill in values
102 va_list vlist;
103 va_start(vlist, query);
104
105 // Get buffer size
106 va_list vlist_copy;
107 va_copy(vlist_copy, vlist);
108 const auto size = vsnprintf(nullptr, 0, query, vlist_copy);
109 va_end(vlist_copy);
110
111 if (size < 0)
112 {
113 va_end(vlist);
114 return nullptr;
115 }
116
117 // save query as prepared
118 std::string preparedQuery(size, '\0');
119 vsnprintf(&preparedQuery[0], static_cast<size_t>(size) + 1, query, vlist);
120 va_end(vlist);
121
122 // checkout additional tables
123 for (const auto& additionalTable : MySQLAdditionalTables)
124 {
125 // query includes table which has additional tables
126 if (AscEmu::Util::Strings::contains(additionalTable.mainTable, preparedQuery))
127 {
128 // add origigin table name to query, replace first occurence of "FROM"
129 std::string originName = ", '" + additionalTable.mainTable + "' as origin FROM";
130 std::string bar = " FROM";
131 size_t pos = preparedQuery.find(bar);
132 size_t len = bar.length();
133 preparedQuery.replace(pos, len, originName);
134 //preparedQuery = std::regex_replace(preparedQuery, std::regex("FROM"), originName);
135
136 // set up new query including the original one
137 std::string completeQuery = preparedQuery;
138
139 if (additionalTable.tableVector.size() > 1)
140 {
141 // go through tables, note: main table is always part of it
142 for (const auto& table : additionalTable.tableVector)
143 {
144 // we already have the query for the main table, if it is an additional table add UNION query
145 if (table != additionalTable.mainTable)
146 {
147 std::string changeQuery = preparedQuery;
148
149 changeQuery = std::regex_replace(changeQuery, std::regex(additionalTable.mainTable), table);
150
151 completeQuery += " UNION ";
152 completeQuery += changeQuery;
153
154 sLogger.debugFlag(AscEmu::Logging::DebugFlags::LF_DB_TABLES, "MySQLDataLoads : Added additional query '{}'", changeQuery);
155 }
156 }
157 }
158
159 sLogger.debugFlag(AscEmu::Logging::DebugFlags::LF_DB_TABLES, "MySQLDataLoads : AdditionalTableLoading - Query: '{}'", completeQuery);
160 return WorldDatabase.Query(completeQuery.c_str());
161 }
162 }
163
164 sLogger.debugFlag(AscEmu::Logging::DebugFlags::LF_DB_TABLES, "MySQLDataLoads : Query: '{}'", preparedQuery);
165 // no additional tables defined, just send our query
166 return WorldDatabase.Query(preparedQuery.c_str());
167}

169void MySQLDataStore::loadItemPagesTable()
170{
171 auto startTime = Util::TimeNow();
172
173 auto itempages_result = WorldDatabase.Query("SELECT entry, text, next_page FROM item_pages");
174 if (itempages_result == nullptr)
175 {
176 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `item_pages` is empty!");
177 return;
178 }
179
180 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `item_pages` has {} columns", itempages_result->GetFieldCount());
181
182 _itemPagesStore.rehash(itempages_result->GetRowCount());
183
184 uint32_t itempages_count = 0;
185 do
186 {
187 Field* fields = itempages_result->Fetch();
188
189 addItemPage(fields[0].asUint32(), fields[1].asCString(), fields[2].asUint32());
190
191 ++itempages_count;
192 } while (itempages_result->NextRow());
193
194 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Loaded {} pages from `item_pages` table in {} ms!", itempages_count, static_cast<uint32_t>(Util::GetTimeDifferenceToNow(startTime)));
195}
196
197void MySQLDataStore::addItemPage(uint32_t _entry, std::string _text, uint32_t _nextPage /*= 0*/)
198{
199 MySQLStructure::ItemPage& itemPage = _itemPagesStore[_entry];
200
201 itemPage.id = _entry;
202 itemPage.text = _text;
203 itemPage.nextPage = _nextPage;
204}
205
206MySQLStructure::ItemPage const* MySQLDataStore::getItemPage(uint32_t entry)
207{
208 ItemPageContainer::const_iterator itr = _itemPagesStore.find(entry);
209 if (itr != _itemPagesStore.end())
210 return &(itr->second);
211
212 return nullptr;
213}
214
215uint32_t MySQLDataStore::getItemPageEntryByText(std::string _text)
216{
217 for (auto itemPage : _itemPagesStore)
218 if (itemPage.second.text == _text)
219 return itemPage.first;
220 return 0;
221}

480void MySQLDataStore::loadItemPropertiesSpellsTable()
481{
482 auto startTime = Util::TimeNow();
483
484 uint32_t spell_count = 0;
485
486 auto item_result = getWorldDBQuery("SELECT * FROM item_properties_spells base "
487 "WHERE build=(SELECT MAX(build) FROM item_properties_spells spec WHERE base.entry = spec.entry AND build <= %u)", VERSION_STRING);
488
489 if (item_result == nullptr)
490 {
491 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `item_properties_spells` is empty!");
492 return;
493 }
494
495 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `item_properties_spells` has {} columns", item_result->GetFieldCount());
496
497 struct LoadItemSpell
498 {
499 uint32_t trigger;
500 int32_t charges;
501 int32_t cooldown;
502 uint32_t category;
503 int32_t categoryCooldown;
504 };
505
506 std::map<uint32_t, std::unordered_map<uint32_t, LoadItemSpell>> tempSpellStore;
507 do
508 {
509 Field* fields = item_result->Fetch();
510
511 uint32_t entry = fields[0].asUint32();
512 uint32_t spellid = fields[2].asUint32();
513
514 LoadItemSpell spellData;
515 spellData.trigger = fields[3].asUint32();
516 spellData.charges = fields[4].asInt32();
517 spellData.cooldown = fields[5].asInt32();
518 spellData.category = fields[6].asUint32();
519 spellData.categoryCooldown = fields[7].asInt32();
520
521 tempSpellStore[entry][spellid] = spellData;
522
523 ++spell_count;
524 } while (item_result->NextRow());
525
526 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Loaded {} item_properties_spells in {} ms!", spell_count, static_cast<uint32_t>(Util::GetTimeDifferenceToNow(startTime)));
527
528
529 startTime = Util::TimeNow();
530 uint32_t assignedCount = 0;
531
532 for (const auto& [entry, bySpellId] : tempSpellStore)
533 {
534 ItemProperties& ip = _itemPropertiesStore[entry];
535
536 size_t i = 0;
537 for (const auto& [spellId, data] : bySpellId)
538 {
539 if (i >= MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SPELLS)
540 break;
541
542 ip.Spells[i].Id = spellId;
543 ip.Spells[i].Trigger = data.trigger;
544 ip.Spells[i].Charges = data.charges;
545 ip.Spells[i].Cooldown = data.cooldown;
546 ip.Spells[i].Category = data.category;
547 ip.Spells[i].CategoryCooldown = data.categoryCooldown;
548
549 ++i;
550 ++assignedCount;
551 }
552 }
553
554 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : assigned {} spells to item_properties in {} ms!", assignedCount, static_cast<uint32_t>(Util::GetTimeDifferenceToNow(startTime)));
555}

557void MySQLDataStore::loadItemPropertiesStatsTable()
558{
559 auto startTime = Util::TimeNow();
560
561 uint32_t stat_count = 0;
562
563 auto item_result = getWorldDBQuery("SELECT * FROM item_properties_stats base "
564 "WHERE build=(SELECT MAX(build) FROM item_properties_stats spec WHERE base.entry = spec.entry AND build <= %u)", VERSION_STRING);
565
566
567 if (item_result == nullptr)
568 {
569 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `item_properties_stats` is empty!");
570 return;
571 }
572
573 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `item_properties_stats` has {} columns", item_result->GetFieldCount());
574
575 std::map<uint32_t, std::map<uint32_t, int32_t>> tempStatsStore;
576 do
577 {
578 Field* fields = item_result->Fetch();
579
580 uint32_t entry = fields[0].asUint32();
581 uint32_t type = fields[2].asUint32();
582 int32_t value = fields[3].asInt32();
583
584 tempStatsStore[entry][type] = value;
585
586 ++stat_count;
587 } while (item_result->NextRow());
588
589 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Loaded {} item_properties_stats in {} ms!", stat_count, static_cast<uint32_t>(Util::GetTimeDifferenceToNow(startTime)));
590
591
592 startTime = Util::TimeNow();
593 uint32_t assignedCount = 0;
594
595 for (const auto& statEntry : tempStatsStore)
596 {
597 uint32_t entry = statEntry.first;
598 const auto& typeMap = statEntry.second;
599
600 ItemProperties& itemProperties = _itemPropertiesStore[entry];
601
602 for (const auto& kv : typeMap)
603 {
604 uint32_t type = kv.first;
605 int32_t value = kv.second;
606
607 itemProperties.addStat(type, value);
608
609 ++assignedCount;
610 }
611 }
612
613 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : assigned {} stats to item_properties in {} ms!", assignedCount, static_cast<uint32_t>(Util::GetTimeDifferenceToNow(startTime)));
614}

627std::string MySQLDataStore::getItemLinkByProto(ItemProperties const* iProto, uint32_t language/* = 0*/)
628{
629 char buffer[256];
630 std::string colour;
631
632 switch (iProto->Quality)
633 {
634 case ITEM_QUALITY_NORMAL: // white
635 colour = "cffffffff";
636 break;
637 case ITEM_QUALITY_UNCOMMON: // green
638 colour = "cff1eff00";
639 break;
640 case ITEM_QUALITY_RARE: // blue
641 colour = "cff0070dd";
642 break;
643 case ITEM_QUALITY_EPIC: // purple
644 colour = "cffa335ee";
645 break;
646 case ITEM_QUALITY_LEGENDARY: // orange
647 colour = "cffff8000";
648 break;
649 case ITEM_QUALITY_ARTIFACT:
650 case ITEM_QUALITY_HEIRLOOM: // gold
651 colour = "c00fce080";
652 break;
653 case ITEM_QUALITY_POOR: // gray
654 default:
655 colour = "cff9d9d9d";
656 }
657
658 // try to get localized version
659 char* lit = (language > 0) ? sMySQLStore.getLocalizedItemName(iProto->ItemId, language) : nullptr;
660 if (lit)
661 snprintf(buffer, 256, "|%s|Hitem:%u:0:0:0:0:0:0:0|h[%s]|h|r", colour.c_str(), iProto->ItemId, lit);
662 else
663 snprintf(buffer, 256, "|%s|Hitem:%u:0:0:0:0:0:0:0|h[%s]|h|r", colour.c_str(), iProto->ItemId, iProto->Name.c_str());
664
665 const char* ItemLink = buffer;
666
667 return ItemLink;
668}

872 continue;

874 else
875 {
876 if ((sp->getAttributes() & ATTRIBUTES_PASSIVE) == 0)
877 creatureProperties.castable_spells.push_back(sp->getId());

879 creatureProperties.start_auras.insert(sp->getId());

894 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < 3; i++)
895 {
896 if (creature_spell_data == nullptr)
897 continue;

899 if (creature_spell_data->Spells[i] == 0)
900 continue;

903 if (sp == nullptr)
904 continue;
905
906 if ((sp->getAttributes() & ATTRIBUTES_PASSIVE) == 0)

923
924 if (origin == "creature_properties_copy")
925 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Loaded {} creature proto from table {}", creatureProperties.Id, origin);
926
927 auto movement = getCreaturePropertiesMovement(entry);
928 if (movement)
929 {
930 creatureProperties.MovementType = movement->MovementType;
931 creatureProperties.Movement.Ground = movement->Movement.Ground;
932 creatureProperties.Movement.Swim = movement->Movement.Swim;
933 creatureProperties.Movement.Flight = movement->Movement.Flight;
934 creatureProperties.Movement.Rooted = movement->Movement.Rooted;
935 creatureProperties.Movement.Chase = movement->Movement.Chase;
936 creatureProperties.Movement.Random = movement->Movement.Random;
937 }

939 {
940 creatureProperties.MovementType = IDLE_MOTION_TYPE;
941 creatureProperties.Movement.Ground = static_cast<CreatureGroundMovementType>(1);
942 creatureProperties.Movement.Swim = false;
943 creatureProperties.Movement.Flight = static_cast<CreatureFlightMovementType>(0);
944 creatureProperties.Movement.Rooted = false;
945 creatureProperties.Movement.Chase = static_cast<CreatureChaseMovementType>(0);
946 creatureProperties.Movement.Random = static_cast<CreatureRandomMovementType>(0);
947 }
948
949 //process aura string
950 if (creatureProperties.aura_string.size() != 0)
951 {
952 std::string auras = creatureProperties.aura_string;
953 std::vector<std::string> split_auras = AscEmu::Util::Strings::split(auras, " ");
954 for (std::vector<std::string>::iterator it = split_auras.begin(); it != split_auras.end(); ++it)
955 {
956 uint32_t id = std::stoul((*it).c_str());
957 if (id)
958 creatureProperties.start_auras.insert(id);
959 }
960 }
961
962 //Itemslot
963 creatureProperties.itemslot_1 = 0;
964 creatureProperties.itemslot_2 = 0;
965 creatureProperties.itemslot_3 = 0;
966
967 /*for (uint8_t i = 0; i < NUM_MONSTER_SAY_EVENTS; ++i)
968 {
969 creatureProperties.MonsterSay[i] = nullptr;
970 }*/
971
972 ++creature_properties_count;
973 } while (creature_properties_result->NextRow());
974
975 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Loaded {} creature proto data in {} ms!", creature_properties_count, static_cast<uint32_t>(Util::GetTimeDifferenceToNow(startTime)));
976}

1592uint32_t MySQLDataStore::getCreatureDifficulty(uint32_t entry, uint8_t difficulty_type)
1593{
1594 for (auto itr = _creatureDifficultyStore.begin(); itr != _creatureDifficultyStore.end(); ++itr)
1595 {
1596 switch (difficulty_type)
1597 {
1598 case 1:
1599 {
1600 if (itr->first == entry && itr->second.difficultyEntry1 != 0)
1601 return itr->second.difficultyEntry1;
1602 }
1603 break;
1604 case 2:
1605 {
1606 if (itr->first == entry && itr->second.difficultyEntry2 != 0)
1607 return itr->second.difficultyEntry2;
1608 }
1609 break;
1610 case 3:
1611 {
1612 if (itr->first == entry && itr->second.difficultyEntry3 != 0)
1613 return itr->second.difficultyEntry3;
1614 }
1615 break;
1616 default:
1617 return 0;
1618 }
1619 }
1620 return 0;

4773void MySQLDataStore::loadCreatureGroupSpawns()
4774{
4775 auto startTime = Util::TimeNow();
4776
4777 _spawnGroupMapStore.clear();
4778
4779 auto result = WorldDatabase.Query("SELECT * FROM creature_group_spawn ORDER BY groupId");
4780 if (result == nullptr)
4781 {
4782 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `creature_group_spawn` is empty!");
4783 return;
4784 }
4785
4786 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `creature_group_spawn` has {} columns", result->GetFieldCount());
4787
4788 uint32_t load_count = 0;
4789 do
4790 {
4791 Field* fields = result->Fetch();
4792 uint32_t groupId = fields[0].asUint8();
4793 uint32_t spawnId = fields[1].asUint32();
4794 bool data = false;
4795
4796 auto it = _spawnGroupDataStore.find(groupId);
4797 if (it == _spawnGroupDataStore.end())
4798 {
4799 sLogger.failure("Spawn group {} assigned to spawn ID ({}), but group does not exist!", groupId, spawnId);
4800 continue;
4801 }
4802
4803 for (const auto& creatureSpawnMap : sMySQLStore._creatureSpawnsStore)
4804 {
4805 for (const auto& creatureSpawn : creatureSpawnMap)
4806 {
4807 if (creatureSpawn->id == spawnId)
4808 {
4809 data = true;
4810
4811 SpawnGroupTemplateData& groupTemplate = it->second;
4812 if (groupTemplate.mapId == 0xFFFFFFFF)
4813 groupTemplate.mapId = creatureSpawn->mapId;
4814
4815 else if (groupTemplate.mapId != creatureSpawn->mapId && !(groupTemplate.groupFlags & SPAWNGROUP_FLAG_SYSTEM))
4816 {
4817 sLogger.debugFlag(AscEmu::Logging::LF_DB_TABLES, "Spawn group {} has map ID {}, but spawn ({}) has map id {} - spawn NOT added to group!", groupId, groupTemplate.mapId, spawnId, creatureSpawn->mapId);
4818 continue;
4819 }
4820
4821 groupTemplate.spawns.insert(std::make_pair(spawnId, nullptr));
4822 _spawnGroupMapStore.emplace(spawnId, &groupTemplate);
4823
4824 ++load_count;
4825 }
4826 }
4827 }
4828
4829 if (!data)
4830 {
4831 sLogger.debugFlag(AscEmu::Logging::LF_DB_TABLES, "Spawn data with ID ({}) not found, but is listed as a member of spawn group {}!", spawnId, groupId);
4832 continue;
4833 }
4834 } while (result->NextRow());
4835
4836 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Loaded {} rows from `creature_group_spawn` table in {} ms!", load_count, static_cast<uint32_t>(Util::GetTimeDifferenceToNow(startTime)));
4837}

4874void MySQLDataStore::loadCreatureSplineChains()
4875{
4876 auto startTime = Util::TimeNow();
4877
4878 _splineChainsStore.clear();
4879
4880 auto resultMeta = WorldDatabase.Query("SELECT entry, chainId, splineId, expectedDuration, msUntilNext, velocity FROM script_spline_chain_meta ORDER BY entry asc, chainId asc, splineId asc");
4881 if (resultMeta == nullptr)
4882 {
4883 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `script_spline_chain_meta` is empty!");
4884 return;
4885 }
4886
4887 auto resultWp = WorldDatabase.Query("SELECT entry, chainId, splineId, wpId, x, y, z FROM script_spline_chain_waypoints ORDER BY entry asc, chainId asc, splineId asc, wpId asc");
4888 if (resultMeta == nullptr)
4889 {
4890 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Table `script_spline_chain_waypoints` is empty!");
4891 return;
4892 }
4893
4894 uint32_t chainCount = 0;
4895 uint32_t splineCount = 0;
4896 uint32_t wpCount = 0;
4897 do
4898 {
4899 Field* fieldsMeta = resultMeta->Fetch();
4900 uint32_t entry = fieldsMeta[0].asUint32();
4901 uint16_t chainId = fieldsMeta[1].asUint16();
4902 uint8_t splineId = fieldsMeta[2].asUint8();
4903 std::vector<SplineChainLink>& chain = _splineChainsStore[{entry, chainId}];
4904
4905 if (splineId != chain.size())
4906 {
4907 sLogger.warning("Creature #{}: Chain {} has orphaned spline {}, skipped.", entry, chainId, splineId);
4908 continue;
4909 }
4910
4911 uint32_t expectedDuration = fieldsMeta[3].asUint32();
4912 uint32_t msUntilNext = fieldsMeta[4].asUint32();
4913 float velocity = fieldsMeta[5].asFloat();
4914 chain.emplace_back(expectedDuration, msUntilNext, velocity);
4915
4916 if (splineId == 0)
4917 ++chainCount;
4918 ++splineCount;
4919 } while (resultMeta->NextRow());
4920
4921 do
4922 {
4923 Field* fieldsWP = resultWp->Fetch();
4924 uint32_t entry = fieldsWP[0].asUint32();
4925 uint16_t chainId = fieldsWP[1].asUint16();
4926 uint8_t splineId = fieldsWP[2].asUint8(), wpId = fieldsWP[3].asUint8();
4927 float posX = fieldsWP[4].asFloat(), posY = fieldsWP[5].asFloat(), posZ = fieldsWP[6].asFloat();
4928 auto it = _splineChainsStore.find({ entry,chainId });
4929 if (it == _splineChainsStore.end())
4930 {
4931 sLogger.warning("Creature #{} has waypoint data for spline chain {}. No such chain exists - entry skipped.", entry, chainId);
4932 continue;
4933 }
4934 std::vector<SplineChainLink>& chain = it->second;
4935 if (splineId >= chain.size())
4936 {
4937 sLogger.warning("Creature #{} has waypoint data for spline ({},{}). The specified chain does not have a spline with this index - entry skipped.", entry, chainId, splineId);
4938 continue;
4939 }
4940 SplineChainLink& spline = chain[splineId];
4941 if (wpId != spline.Points.size())
4942 {
4943 sLogger.warning("Creature #{} has orphaned waypoint data in spline ({},{}) at index {}. Skipped.", entry, chainId, splineId, wpId);
4944 continue;
4945 }
4946 spline.Points.emplace_back(posX, posY, posZ);
4947 ++wpCount;
4948 } while (resultWp->NextRow());
4949
4950 sLogger.info("MySQLDataLoads : Loaded spline chain data for {} chains, consisting of {} splines with {} waypoints in {} ms!", chainCount, splineCount, wpCount, static_cast<uint32_t>(Util::GetTimeDifferenceToNow(startTime)));
4951}

4954{
4955 auto it = _splineChainsStore.find({ entry, chainId });
4956 if (it == _splineChainsStore.end())
4957 return nullptr;
4958
4959 return &it->second;
4960}
